current-chamber.#text: IN THE SENATE OF THE UNITED STATES

official-title.#text:
To amend title 23, United States Code, with respect to
		  the operation of vehicles on certain Wisconsin highways, and for other
		  purposes.

committee-name.#text:
Committee on Environment and Public
			 Works

cosponsor.#tail:
) introduced
			 the following bill; which was read twice and referred to the

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail:
,
			 is amended by adding at the end the following:

header.#text:
Operation of vehicles on
			 certain Wisconsin highways

text.#text:
If any segment of the
				United States Route 41 corridor, as described in

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail:
is designated as a route on the Interstate System, a vehicle that
				could operate legally on that segment before the date of that designation may
				continue to operate on that segment, without regard to any requirement under

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#text:
section 1105(c)(57) of the
				Intermodal Surface Transportation Efficiency Act of 1991
{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.@value: Intermodal Surface Transportation Efficiency Act of 1991/s:1105/ss:c/p:57

header.#text:
Operation of
				vehicles on certain Wisconsin highways
